Homepage: https://github.com/MX-Linux/mx-conky

Package: mx-conky
Architecture: any
Depends: mx-conky-data-bin,
	conky-all | conky,
	${misc:Depends},
	${shlibs:Depends}
Recommends: mx-conky-data,
	graphicsmagick-imagemagick-compat
Description: Conky configuration tool for MX Linux
 MX Conky is a graphical tool used for configuring and managing Conky
 on MX Linux. It allows users to easily customize Conky displays by
 manipulating detailed attributes such as colors, formats, transparency,
 and positioning. The tool provides a user-friendly interface for both
 beginners and advanced users to create and modify Conky configurations
 without manual editing of configuration files.
